Fuji music star, Wasiu Alabi aka Pasuma led his colleagues and top-tier celebrities to the private screening of Sule Alao Malaika’s debut movie entitled, ‘Alao Oje.’ The event, which was held on Sunday at the Radisson Blu, Ikeja, had Yoruba actor and film director Murphy Afolabi, Adekola Tijani amongst others in attendance. Speaking ahead of the official release of the Yoruba epic film, the ‘Original’ singer said his acting dexterity will amaze his music fans.   Young Jonn joins Chocolate City, releases new single     Niyi Johnson, Omowunmi Dada feature in Rebirth     RITA DOMINIC: How I get in and out of emotional scenes   “It’s something different and explicit from me to amaze my fans both home and abroad. I have featured in a couple of movies but this is different,” Malaika said. Continuing he said, “This is something I have never done before. So you all should keep your fingers crossed and wait on it for me to blow your mind.” According to the Fuji star, another private screening will hold in the United States of America and other countries to honour his fans, Alayeluwa Worldwide before it will be released for public consumption. The premiere was packaged by The T Pumpy Concept.